    <title>Generalized Koszul properties of commutative local rings</title>
    <summary>  We study several properties of commutative local rings that generalize the
notion of Koszul algebra. The properties are expressed in terms of the Ext
algebra of the ring, or in terms of homological properties of powers of the
maximal ideal of the ring. We analyze relationships between these properties
and we identify large classes of rings that satisfy them. In particular, we
prove that the Ext algebra of a compressed Gorenstein local ring of even socle
degree is generated in degrees $1$ and $2$.
</summary>
